Fired when a full LDAP import contains user and/or group objects with a missing modifyTimeStamp value. This can be used to identify whether or not a subsequent incremental import will not update objects imported in a full import. Any object with a missing modifyTimeStamp value at the time of a subsequent incremental import will not be updated. Note that in this case, the import will not fail, Okta will simply not update the objects with a missing modifyTimeStamp value. Any missing modifyTimeStamp values need to be addressed in the LDAP server, not in Okta. When fired, this event contains information on how many objects are missing the modifyTimeStamp value and the associated import event.
